two patients instead of one.

252
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:19,584
We can't just close her up.

253
00:20:19,652 --> 00:20:21,120
Unfortunately, we can.

254
00:20:23,022 --> 00:20:26,151
I'm sorry, but you've
never led anything like this.

255
00:20:29,762 --> 00:20:31,958
I think we should
let her keep going.

256
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:34,295
- What's the worst that could happen?
- Beyond death?

257
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,962
This patient was gonna die anyway.
Claire gives her a fighting chance.

258
00:20:45,111 --> 00:20:46,111
Okay.

259
00:20:50,783 --> 00:20:52,274
What happened...

260
00:20:54,186 --> 00:20:55,984
with the ventilator?

261
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:59,650
They took it. They
needed it for the surgery.

262
00:21:00,326 --> 00:21:03,785
The doctors needed it.

263
00:21:03,863 --> 00:21:05,832
The doctors needed it?

264
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:08,667
And where's the nurse?

265
00:21:09,502 --> 00:21:10,993
The nurse?

266
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:14,096
Busy, lots of work.

267
00:21:15,141 --> 00:21:16,141
Okay.

268
00:21:17,309 --> 00:21:18,868
I'll stay.

269
00:21:18,978 --> 00:21:21,948
Stay <i>aqu√≠.</i> No matter
how long it takes.

270
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:30,317
- Is there a problem?
- Yes, the patient came back.

271
00:21:39,365 --> 00:21:41,357
Le√≥n, the guy
with ventral hernia,

272
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:44,699
