unless we operate on him.

276
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:54,712
Can you fit him in after
your skull reconstruction?

277
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:57,909
Not without big risks to both of
them. What about the other surgeons?

278
00:21:58,017 --> 00:22:00,043
You think I'd be here if
anyone else was free?

279
00:22:02,388 --> 00:22:03,515
Give him some morphine.

280
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:05,514
Until when?

281
00:22:06,192 --> 00:22:08,684
It sucks, but it's his fault.
We told him he needed to rest.

282
00:22:08,761 --> 00:22:11,731
This isn't some tech bro in San
Francisco waltzing out to party.

283
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:14,699
He needed to keep his job
and not watch his family starve.

284
00:22:14,767 --> 00:22:18,329
If we operate on him, we
don't operate on someone else.

285
00:22:22,274 --> 00:22:23,537
I'll operate on Le√≥n.

286
00:22:24,877 --> 00:22:27,437
I've been doing PT the last
year. It's been going great.

287
00:22:27,546 --> 00:22:29,447
You really think you
can handle the surgery?

288
00:22:30,583 --> 00:22:31,583
I know I can.

289
00:22:32,051 --> 00:22:34,646
I think I can do it
without any pain.

290
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:45,224
We need to do a
cross-clamp resection.

291
00:22:45,297 --> 00:22:46,788
Have you ever done one?

292
00:22:46,899 --> 00:22:48,891
I've seen one when
I was an intern.

293
00:22:56,275 --> 00:22:57,800
Freeing up the vein.

294
00:23:03,782 --> 00:23:05,614
Dividing the pedicles.

295
00:23:09,421 --> 00:23:10,480
Uh...

296
00:23:11,924 --> 00:23:13,415
Transecting the segments.

297
00:23:29,742 --> 00:23:30,742
Step two.

298
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,108
That doesn't look ideal.

299
00:23:39,218 --> 00:23:41,153
It's a midline ventral defect.

300
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:44,485
Also, the tissue
planes are friable.

301
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:46,786
We're gonna need
component separation.

302
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,619
We cut the posterior
rectus sheath,

303
00:23:50,729 --> 00:23:54,757
mobilizing soft tissue off of
the external oblique fascia...

304
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:57,497
and then incise it.

305
00:24:03,142 --> 00:24:05,839
Common femoral artery's
almost completely occluded.

306
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:08,141
I'll prep the inflow
anastomosis site.

307
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,810
I have PTSD.

308
00:24:17,389 --> 00:24:18,948
I have nightmares because of it.

309
00:24:19,024 --> 00:24:21,152
I exercise to help me
manage my symptoms.

310
00:24:21,260 --> 00:24:23,695
And the alarm on my
phone is to remind me

311
00:24:23,796 --> 00:24:27,699
to take my daily cocktail of
fluoxetine, prazosin and quetiapine.

312
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:31,398
Can you tunnel the bypass
graft in the subcutaneous plane?

313
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:34,136
I'll get a clamp through.

314
00:24:36,075 --> 00:24:39,705
I lost a good friend a year ago

315
00:24:40,479 --> 00:24:42,141
and then lost more to COVID...

316
00:24:43,082 --> 00:24:47,213
and then spent a lot of
time denying I had an issue.

317
00:24:49,822 --> 00:24:51,222
Running from pain.

318
00:24:55,094 --> 00:24:58,496
In the future, I'm hoping to
do more running toward things

319
00:24:58,564 --> 00:24:59,793
than away from them.

320
00:25:04,403 --> 00:25:05,837
I'm ready for the graft.

321
00:25:26,392 --> 00:25:27,690
Oh, it's my turn.

322
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:30,389
You're exhausted.
You should lie down.

323
00:25:30,462 --> 00:25:32,055
No. No.

324
00:25:32,131 --> 00:25:33,429
Ten minutes.

325
00:25:36,568 --> 00:25:37,467
I'm good.

326
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:39,197
I'll rest next.

327
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:45,410
Ten minutes.

328
00:25:47,246 --> 00:25:48,246
Thank you.

329
00:26:03,929 --> 00:26:05,898
- If you need a break...
- I'm fine.

330
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:08,456
Just cramped a little.

331
00:26:11,437 --> 00:26:12,437
I'm done.

332
00:26:17,109 --> 00:26:18,407
I can take over.

333
00:26:33,692 --> 00:26:36,127
This ventral wall
defect is huge.

334
00:26:37,963 --> 00:26:38,963
Yeah.

335
00:26:46,405 --> 00:26:47,771
Two Kocher clamps.

336
00:27:29,014 --> 00:27:31,848
- Heart rate is spiking.
- BP's dropping. She's crashing.

337
00:27:31,950 --> 00:27:33,441
Why? What happened?

338
00:27:35,387 --> 00:27:36,387
I don't know.

339
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:44,830
Edna's bleeding out. At this
rate, she has minutes to live.

340
00:27:44,897 --> 00:27:47,230
There was post-op blood
around the liver, nothing crazy.

341
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:50,393
The surgical drain also has
blood, no evidence of bile leak.

342
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:54,997
