An intrahepatic bleed
is statistically more likely.

350
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:19,996
I still think it's the stomach.

351
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:23,526
But I came to you for
a reason, okay, thanks.

352
00:28:23,602 --> 00:28:24,602
Claire.

353
00:28:26,238 --> 00:28:29,265
Neither of us
knows for sure, but...

354
00:28:31,610 --> 00:28:33,101
you are good at this.

355
00:28:35,147 --> 00:28:36,547
Better than you think.

356
00:28:44,823 --> 00:28:47,224
BP's almost bottomed
out. What do we do?

357
00:28:49,394 --> 00:28:50,394
Stomach.

358
00:29:00,539 --> 00:29:01,837
You did good work.

359
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:04,569
I just had to close
and clean up.

360
00:29:05,244 --> 00:29:07,475
The patient's in
recovery, doing well.

361
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:16,915
I need a friend.

362
00:29:24,663 --> 00:29:28,566
I hadn't really given
up on being a surgeon.

363
00:29:29,701 --> 00:29:31,567
PT was going great.

364
00:29:32,971 --> 00:29:34,997
Almost no pain at all until...

365
00:29:37,175 --> 00:29:39,144
It's all dumb, because...

366
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:42,304
I like being an
internist. I just...

367
00:29:45,851 --> 00:29:46,851
hate...

368
00:29:49,855 --> 00:29:51,016
failing.

369
00:29:56,962 --> 00:29:59,454
Seriously? This is funny?

370
00:30:01,199 --> 00:30:02,199
A little.

371
00:30:03,468 --> 00:30:05,130
Never seen you vulnerable.

372
00:30:07,506 --> 00:30:10,601
Your face gets kind of ugly.

373
00:30:12,678 --> 00:30:13,678
Shut up.

374
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:16,614
You didn't fail.

375
00:30:19,618 --> 00:30:20,847
You never fail.

376
00:30:22,654 --> 00:30:26,147
For three years, I've
